      public Event(String title, String uid, String date_time, String location, String registration_start, String registration_deadline, String details, boolean track_geolocation, boolean will_automatically_redraw, int waitlist_limit, int attendee_limit, String organizer)
      Creates an Event without an image
      Parameters:
      title - title of event
      uid - uid of event
      date_time - date and time of the Event
      location - location of the Event
      registration_start - registration start time of event
      registration_deadline - registration deadline of an event
      details - details and information about an Event such as: topic, difficulty, age range etc.
      track_geolocation - whether the Event would like to track the waitlist Entrants location
      will_automatically_redraw - whether the Event will immediately redraw an Entrant from the waitlist to be added to the invited list
      waitlist_limit - maximum amount of Entrants in a waitlist
      attendee_limit - maximum amount of Entrant that will attend the event
      organizer - organizer of event

    • doLottery

      public void doLottery() throws InterruptedException
      Conducts a lottery draw: randomly selects a number of entrants from the waitlist (up to available attendee spots), removes them from the waitlist, and moves them to the invited list. Then it sends an invitation to all of the entrants that are invited to join the event, and sends a rejection to entrants who were not invited to join the event
      Throws:
      InterruptedException
